trend_summary: Built-up land expands steadily southeastward, doubling since the earliest image while ribbon development creeps north along main roads. Most of the county stays forest or pasture, though several clearings, a larger reservoir and new roads accompany suburban growth. Overall character remains rural with sparse, clustered construction.
notable_changes: Built-up footprint in the southeast almost doubles, forming a larger continuous settlement.
New housing subdivisions spread north and west, replacing pockets of woodland.
Agricultural patches contract and shift, with some areas transitioning to secondary forest.
Southern reservoir enlarged; adjacent banks show fresh construction and road access.
